summary: An ordinance relating to and providing for the licensing and regulating of the traffic of intoxicating and malt liquors within the City of Seattle, and providing penalties for violations thereof, and repealing all ordinances or parts of ordinances in conflict herewith 16324, entitled: "An ordinance providing for the licensing and regulating of the traffic in intoxicating malt liquors within the City of Seattle and providing penalties for violation thereof" approved June 19, 1907; Ordinance No. 17789, entitled: "An ordinance regulating the traffic in intoxicating and malt liquors within the City of Seattle on the day of any primary election, and providing penalties for violation thereof", approved January 31, 1908; and Ordinance No. 24657 entitled: "An ordinance amending Section 16 of Ordinance No. 16324 entitled: \`An ordinance providing for the licensing and regulating of the traffic in intoxicating malt liquors within the City of Seattle and providing penalties for violation thereof' approved June 19, 1907" approved July 25, 1910.
